<p>&#8220;Privatized social security in Britain and Chile have administrative costs of this amount (ch. 9, fn. 2), as do private insurers who issue annuities, which seems like the appropriate comparison to a system like social security (ch. 9, fn. 3).&#8221;</p>

<p>The fact that very inefficient systems exist is not a knock against the private investment sector in general.  (Which, as I said, provides options that are <em>more</em> efficient than the social security system).  You can&#8217;t criticize a category by picking on the worst exemplar(s) of that category.</p>

