<p>So, I spent 5 minutes looking for private, fixed-rate annuities, and found one (http://personal.fidelity.com/products/annuities/income/freedom.shtml.cvsr) that has 0.6% charges and roughly 0.85% overhead.  Granted, that&#8217;s about 3x the overhead of SS, but it&#8217;s a hell of lot less than your FUD figure of 20%, and this is also <em>the absolute first fixed-rate annuity I found</em>.  Presumably a bit of shopping around would get you a lower rate.</p>

