<div id="c11">
<p>Some of these seem half-plausible, but the accusations about the Fed are just plain silly. Inflation is far more harmful to an economy than a recession (or slow growth, as we usually see) and so it makes perfect sense for economic policy to err on the more conservative side. If you look at the rate of economic expansions and contractions compared to before the Fed had real teeth, you&#8217;ll see they&#8217;re actually doing an amazing job at guiding something which is inherently extremely difficult to influence.</p>

